com.github.crashdemons.playerheads

Enum TexturedSkullType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TexturedSkullType>
      • com.github.crashdemons.playerheads.TexturedSkullType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TexturedSkullType>

    public enum TexturedSkullType
extends Enum<TexturedSkullType>
    Enumeration of skulls with associated UUID (randomly assigned) and texture string. This enum should match correspondingly named entries in bukkit EntityType enum. Inspired by shininet-CustomSkullType, presumably by meiskam
    Author:
    crashdemons, MagmaVoid_

      • getDisplayName

        public static String getDisplayName(String owner)
        Gets the item displayname for a specific playerhead owner by username. Note: This method is for resolving the displayname of PLAYER head drops, it does not support legacy username-based mobhead displaynames.
        Parameters:
        owner - The username to get a displayname for
        Returns:
        A string containing the user's head displayname

      • getSpawnName

        public String getSpawnName()
        Get the "spawn" name for the associated skulltype, as defined in the "lang" file. This string is used to spawn-in the skull in external commands.
        Returns:
        A string containing the spawnname.

      • isPlayerHead

        public boolean isPlayerHead()
        Checks whether the skulltype uses a playerhead exclusively. This indicates that either the skulltype is PLAYER or a mob without a vanilla head item, generally.
        Returns:
        true: the skulls associated material was a playerhead. false: the skull has a different associated material.

      • hasDedicatedItem

        public boolean hasDedicatedItem()
        Checks whether the skulltype uses a specific material/item specific to it. This indicates wither the skulltype is PLAYER (PLAYERHEAD is dedicated to it), or it has a vanilla head item associated with it, generally.
        Returns:
        true: the skulltype has a dedicated item/material or is of type PLAYER. false: the skulltype is supported as a playerhead (the mob has no special item/material associated).
